                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1231/110: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-07T16:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 7, 1934—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Minister of Foreign Affairs advised me this morning that the Mexican Embassy
                    in Washington is fully prepared to discuss immediately details of a reciprocal
                    tariff agreement and that he hoped the Department would initiate negotiations at
                    an early date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
